cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible sub-category as the paper proposes new methods for analyzing multilayer networks, which could be useful in software engineering for analyzing complex software systems. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category as the paper discusses algorithms for projecting nodes in a network into a continuous vector space, which is a common task in machine learning. 

cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely sub-category, but it could be applicable as the paper discusses analyzing the interactions among different layers in a complex system. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a less likely sub-category, but it could be applicable as the paper discusses graph mining and proposes new methods for analyzing multilayer networks.
